# PROJECT CONTEXT
- Game: Tactical Duelist — players program hero actions simultaneously, then watch execution
- Platform: Unity WebGL → Telegram Mini App (TMA)  
- Perspective: Top-down 2D grid-based (isometric optional later)
- Core loop: Plan actions → Commit hash → Reveal → Resolve simultaneously → Replay
- Match: up to 3 rounds, First Blood (1 HP system)
- 12 asymmetric heroes with varied parameters (Steps, Range, Cooldown, Armor, Speed, Special)

# ARCHITECTURE PRINCIPLES
- Use ScriptableObjects for hero definitions, map configs, and game data
- Use interfaces for action types (IAction, IShootAction, IMoveAction, ISpecialAction)
- Use enums for directions (Up, Down, Left, Right), action types, game states
- Separate game logic from presentation (Model-View pattern)
- Game logic must be deterministic and server-reproducible
- NO MonoBehaviour for game logic — only for Unity integration layer
- Use events/delegates for decoupling (NOT direct references between systems)

# CODE STANDARDS
- C# 9+ features OK (pattern matching, records for data)
- PascalCase for public members, _camelCase for private fields
- [SerializeField] for inspector-exposed private fields
- Use #regions to organize: Constants, Fields, Properties, Unity Lifecycle, Public, Private
- XML doc comments on public methods
- Null-safe: always check references, use ?. operator

# GAME-SPECIFIC RULES
- Grid coordinates: Vector2Int (col, row). Origin bottom-left.
- Facing: enum Direction { Up, Down, Left, Right }
- Actions per round: hero.Steps (3-6), programmed as List<ActionType>
- Shoot = instant raycast on grid, range = hero.Range tiles
- Movement = hero.Speed tiles in facing direction
- Simultaneous resolution: Phase1 Movement → Phase2 Combat → Phase3 Damage
- Mutual hit = both cancel (nobody takes damage)
- Armor: absorbs 1 hit then breaks (bool hasArmor)

# STEP RESOLUTION ORDER (CRITICAL - this is the core mechanic)
Each step within a round resolves in this exact order:
  Phase 1 - MOVEMENT: Both players' Move/Turn actions execute simultaneously
    -> Players arrive at new positions
    -> Collision check: both to same tile = both stay at original
    -> Pickup check: land on item = collected
  Phase 2 - COMBAT: Both players' Shoot/Special actions execute simultaneously  
    -> Shoot: instant ray from CURRENT position (after movement) in facing direction
    -> Ray travels [hero.Range] tiles, blocked by walls
    -> Hit check: does ray pass through tile where opponent currently stands?
  Phase 3 - DAMAGE:
    -> One hit: if target has Armor -> Armor destroyed; else -> ELIMINATED
    -> Both hit: MUTUAL CANCEL (both shots nullified, nobody takes damage)
    -> Neither hit: continue to next step

