# FOLDER STRUCTURE
Assets/
  Scripts/
    Core/          # Game logic (pure C#, no MonoBehaviour)
      Models/      # Hero, Action, Match, Round data classes
      Systems/     # ActionResolver, MatchManager, GridSystem
      Config/      # ScriptableObject definitions
    Gameplay/      # MonoBehaviour wrappers, input handling
    UI/            # UI controllers, screens
    Networking/    # Match networking, hash commitment
    Utils/         # Extensions, helpers
  ScriptableObjects/
    Heroes/        # HeroConfig assets (one per hero)
    Maps/          # MapConfig assets
  Prefabs/
  Art/
  Audio/

# WEBGL CONSTRAINTS
- No System.Threading (use coroutines or UniTask)
- No File I/O (use PlayerPrefs or server)
- Minimize garbage allocation (object pooling, avoid LINQ in hot paths)
- Target 60fps on mobile browsers
- Bundle size matters — no unnecessary packages

# WHAT TO AVOID
- Do NOT use Update() for game logic — use event-driven architecture
- Do NOT use FindObjectOfType or GameObject.Find — use DI or SerializeField
- Do NOT allocate in hot paths (ToString, string concat, LINQ in Update)
- Do NOT use physics engine for grid movement — use pure grid math
- Do NOT hardcode hero stats — always reference ScriptableObjects
- Do NOT use Camera.main (cache it)
- Do NOT use Resources.Load (use Addressables or direct references)
